Problem
Count the number of set bits (1s) in the binary representation of a given integer. The input is an integer n, and the output should be an integer representing the number of set bits in the binary representation of n.

Input Format
An integer n (0 ≤ n ≤ 10^9).

Output Format
An integer representing the number of set bits.

Sample Inputs & Outputs
Sample Input 1

15
Sample Output 1

4
Constraints
0 ≤ n ≤ 10^9

Code:
import java.util.Scanner;

public class CountSetBits {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        // Count the number of 1s in the binary representation
        int count = Integer.bitCount(n);
        System.out.println(count);
    }
}
